Titolo: Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde (video game)

Anno: 1988

Descrizione: Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde is a 1988 side-scrolling action video game for the Nintendo Entertainment System loosely based on the 1886 novella Strange Case of Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde by Robert Louis Stevenson. Gameplay alternates between the characters of Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde based on the player's ability to either avoid or cause damage. The game initially got mixed reception, but retrospective reviews have been more negative. Its title screen uses music from the wise man stage in Rygar.

